Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Halve @orange{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a small, #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine ¼ of the onion, juice from half the lime, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a @salt{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside.

In a separate #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with @southwest spice blend{1/4%tbsp} (½ tsp for 4). (You'll use the remaining Southwest Spice Blend later.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and remaining onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce} and remaining @southwest spice blend{3/4%tbsp}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, juice from orange, and a squeeze of lime juice. Bring to a simmer and cook until pork is cooked through and sauce has thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Swap in beef for pork.

While pork cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between #plates{} and fill with pork filling and veggies. Drizzle with crema and top with pickled onion (draining first) and cilantro. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.